leads.lead_text: Flower 1 per bract; fruit indehiscent, either an achene, a small nut or a drupe
Flowers 2 per bract; fruit a leathery or woody 2-several-seeded follicle opening in 2 valves
Fruit an achene or small nut; ovary sessile, ovule 1; flowers sessile
Fruit a stalked drupe to c. 1 cm long or more; ovary stipitate, ovules usually 2; flowers pedicellate
Flowers densely aggregated into cones or in loose corymbs; leaves simple or 2–3-times pinnatisect with flattened segments
Inflorescences 1-flowered, subsessile, solitary or up to 3 clustered at branch-tips and closely surrounded by leaves; leaves deeply dissected with terete segments; mallee areas of north-west
Flowers white or bluish, arranged in loose corymbs; perianth more or less bilabiate; style not exserted, glabrous; leaves simple; fruit a small hairy achene
Flowers yellow, arranged in cones; perianth regular; style exserted, with brushlike hairs; leaves pinnatisect; fruit a pilose nut subtended by caducous woody bracts combined into a fragile cone
[link through]
Flowers arranged in very dense spikes; fruit 2-valved; mature follicles persistent on and partially embedded in an erect woody axis; seeds 2 per follicle
Flowers not as above; fruiting follicles stalked or sessile, but not embedded in fruiting axis; seeds 2 or more per follicle
Flowers in terminal and upper axils; perianth regular, tepals free or almost so; anthers on short filaments; shrub of alpine areas
Flowers not or rarely in terminal spikes (if inflorescence terminal then plants not alpine); perianth irregular, tepals at least partially joined; anthers sessile
Seeds 2 per follicle, collateral
Seeds usually more than 2 per follicle, in 2 imbricate rows
Follicle leathery; seeds commonly winged all round (or if wing at 1 end only, then wing shorter than seed)
Follicle woody, opening into 2 thick valves; seeds with a large dark terminal wing longer than body of seed
Flowers red; inflorescence a large, hemispherical to globular head surrounded by an involucre of enlarged red bracts; East Gippsland only
Flowers white, cream or yellowish (in Victoria); inflorescence not as above; widespread
Inflorescence raceme-like or paniculate; seeds not as above
Inflorescence umbel-like; seeds with an outer membranous wing folded around the inner wing
